During that time we've released some of TV's most beloved gems such as Freaks And Geeks My So-Called Life Sports Night MadTV and Mystery Science Theater. We've also reintroduced some of television's most adored personalities with collections featuring Dick Cavett Tom Snyder Jack Paar Johnny Carson Mel Brooks Groucho Marx and Elvira Mistress of the Night.

We've reissued the catalogs of Herb Alpert Emerson Lake and Palmer James Brown and John Lee Hooker plus released a slew of new albums including recordings by Matthew Sweet Solomon Burke Local H and Thelma Houston.

title: Mark Redshaw
description: I've always been a huge fan of  the Pet Shop Boys since first hearing West End Girls in the autumn of 1985.

url: After that I bought every 7" and 12" (and imports) the day they were released (usually skipping school to do so!).
I'm not so obsessive these days. From the mid nineties onwards I didn't bother with singles any more I just bought the albums. But I've still got my big box of vinyl and it's pure gold my friends...

So this is a small selection of some of the classic tracks by the Pet Shop Boys that I've managed to collect over the years. They aren't necessarily their best songs (some are - some aren't) - I'm just uploading the stuff that was commercially released but doesn't already have 100 other videos on YouTube.
If anybody wants any particular version or mix of a track that I have just let me know and I'll upload it onto this channel.
